          "notes": "Strong conceptual foundation with excellent real-world cases (BuzzFeed, Samsung, Air Canada, Sweetgreen) that ground abstract AI concepts in actionable lessons. Quizzes test judgment and application well. Labs are well-framed but lack concrete execution scaffolding—instructions describe what learners should do but don't fully specify how to complete tasks or validate success. The AI assistant interface is mentioned but not detailed, creating ambiguity about actual capability.",
          "topIssue": "Labs lack sufficient execution clarity and validation criteria. Lab 1 asks learners to 'ask the assistant' a question but doesn't specify how to evaluate whether the answer is correct or complete. Lab 2 asks learners to describe their business and get filtered recommendations, but there's no rubric or checklist to confirm the bottleneck audit was done properly. Lab 3 and Lab 4 suffer similarly—learners could submit vague prompts and receive unhelpful outputs without knowing the work wasn't done correctly. Add a 'success checklist' to each lab and provide 1-2 worked examples showing strong vs. weak submissions.",
